cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CV 

The paper proposes a new pseudo-random number generator for information security applications like cryptography, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. The paper also mentions an application in the field of watermarking, which could indicate that it belongs to the cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-categories. The use of chaotic iterations suggests that it could also belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-categories.
